> This chicken dish is simple but summery. Chicken, new potatoes and green beans,
> all finished off with a creamy sauce featuring tarragon and Dijon mustard.
> They're perfect partners but strong flavours so only add a bit at a time,
> tasting as you go. Remember the golden rule of cookery - you can add but you
> can't take away! Trust your own palette and we're sure you'll love the result.

Preheat your oven to 220°C. Chop the @salad potatoes{350%g} into 2cm chunks
(no need to peel). Trim the @green beans{150%g}(trimmed). Pick the
@tarragon{½%bunch} leaves from their stalks and finely chop (discard the
stalks).

Place the potatoes on a lined #baking tray{} and drizzle over a little
@oil{}. Season with a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Toss to coat, then
spread out evenly and roast on the top shelf of your oven until crispy,
turning halfway through cooking, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Lay your @British chicken breasts{2} on a #chopping board{}, place your hand
flat on top and slice into it from the side (being careful not to slice all the
way through). Open it up like a book. Repeat for the other breast(s). You've
now butterflied your chicken! Lay the chicken between two sheets of
#clingfilm{} and bash it with a #rolling pin{} or the base of a #pan{} until
it is 1cm thick.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Put a large #saucepan{} of water with a @salt{pinch} on to boil for the green
beans. Heat a splash of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium/high heat. Season
the chicken on both sides with a @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. Once the
oil is hot, fry the chicken for ~{4-6%minutes} on each side, then remove the
pan from the heat.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Add the green beans to the pan of boiling water. Boil until tender,
~{4-5%minutes}. Once cooked, drain the beans in a #colander{} and set aside.

Meanwhile, put the frying pan with your chicken in back on medium heat.
Add the @creme fraiche{50%g}, a splash of water and the @Dijon mustard{1%tsp}.
Bubble gently until you have the consistency of double cream, then remove from
the heat and stir in the tarragon.

> TIP: If you don't like tarragon, add a little less!

Serve the roasted new potatoes and the green beans with the chicken on top
and a healthy spoonful of your tarragon sauce. Enjoy!